HEADWORD: Catacrotic
<hw>Cat`a*crot"ic</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos>
<ety>[<ets>Cata-</ets> + Gr. <?/ a beating.]</ety> <fld>(Physiol.)</fld>
<def>Designating, pertaining to, or characterized by, that form of pulse
tracing, or sphygmogram, in which the descending portion of the curve is
marked by secondary elevations due to two or more expansions of the
artery in the same beat.</def> -- <wordforms><wf>Ca*tac"rotism</wf>
<pr>(#)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos></wordforms>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

